'''Pua Khein-Seng''' ({{zh|潘健成}}; born 29 June 1974, is arguably one of the inventors of [[USB flash drive]]. In an interview with ''[[The Star (Malaysia)|The Star]]'', the CEO of [[Phison Electronics Corporation|Phison Electronics Corp]] based in [[Taiwan]] claims to have incorporated the world's first single chip [[USB flash drive]]. He is even regarded as "father of pendrive" in Malaysia.<ref>{{cite news|last=Lee|first=Kian Seong|title=Up close & personal with Pua Khein-Seng|url=http://biz.thestar.com.my/news/story.asp?file=/2009/9/5/business/4602288&sec=business|newspaper=The Star|date=September 5, 2009}}</ref> Raised in [[Sekinchan]], [[Selangor]], [[Malaysia]],<ref name="sekinchan">{{cite web|title=Press Digest - Pen-drive man laments shortage of local talent {{!}} theSundaily|url=http://www.thesundaily.my/news/1126774|website=www.thesundaily.my|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref> Pua received his undergraduate education in electrical control engineering at the [[National Chiao Tung University]], [[Taiwan]] and has since then resided in Taiwan.<ref name="universitytaiwan">{{cite web|title=Something from nothing - SMEBiz Focus {{!}} The Star Online|url=http://www.thestar.com.my/metro/smebiz/focus/2015/10/05/something-from-nothing/|website=www.thestar.com.my|accessdate=9 December 2016}}</ref>

